This point has fueled the necessity for change in this legislative environment.  
It is also why the proposed changes in Bill C-5 mirror some of the existing rights for businesses which are granted under the Canada Business Corporations Act. 
Thus it is called enabling legislation. 
Powers are expanded and existing rules are clarified, but no co-operative is forced to change the way it currently operates.  
