I would like to point out that Bill C-5 is not a controversial bill. 
I believe a reasonable compromise was reached. 
Overall this bill is a positive step in bringing co-operatives into the 21st century by making them more flexible, more efficient and more competitive.  
The changes in Bill C-5 are wide scale adjustments but I am confident the overall co-op membership of some 4.5 million Canadians will benefit greatly.  
